## Part 3: GitHub Fix — Large Files in Git History

### What Happened

The error `pre-receive hook declined` means GitHub is **rejecting your push** because your repository contains files larger than GitHub's 100MB limit.

Looking at your git history, I found the culprit — a **`Resumes/` folder** with massive zip files:

| File | Size |
|------|------|
| `Resumes/Resume.zip` | **329 MB** 🚨 |
| `Resumes/OneDrive_2026-04-17 (1)666.zip` | **173 MB** 🚨 |
| `Resumes/OneDrive_2026-04.zip` | **24 MB** |
| `Resumes/Kusto-Devops-Azure-C#.zip` | **9 MB** |

Even though you added `Resumes` to `.gitignore`, the files are **already committed in past git history**. `.gitignore` only prevents *future* tracking — it doesn't remove files from past commits.

### The Fix

We need to **rewrite git history** to remove these files permanently. This uses `git filter-branch` or the cleaner `git filter-repo` tool.

> [!CAUTION]
> This rewrites all commit hashes. If anyone else has cloned the repo, they'll need to re-clone. Since it's your personal project, this is fine.

